            "subject": "LU-9490 llite: return v1/v3 layout for legacy app"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Bobi Jam",
          "email": "bobijam.xu@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-05-16 12:37:20.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-05-31 04:27:52.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9484 llite: eat -EEXIST on setting trusted.lov",
        "message": "LU-9484 llite: eat -EEXIST on setting trusted.lov\n\nTools like rsync, tar, cp may copy and restore the xattrs on a file.\nThe client previously ignored the setting of trusted.lov/lustre.lov\nif the layout had already been specified, to avoid causing these\ntools to fail for no reason.\n\nFor PFL files we still need to silently eat -EEXIST on setting these\nattributes to avoid problems.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam.xu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ic6d359c0f3557d4a21e950a53f57e38ae97a40da\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/pfl"
    }
  },
